1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,648
2 Timothy 3. This know also, that in the last days perilous times shall come.

2
00:00:06,648 --> 00:00:14,735
For men shall be lovers of their own selves, covetous, boasters, proud, blasphemers, disobedient to parents, unthankful,

3
00:00:14,735 --> 00:00:22,727
unholy, Without natural affection, trucebreakers, false accusers, incontinent, fierce, despisers of those that are good,

4
00:00:22,727 --> 00:00:30,432
Traitors, heady, highminded, lovers of pleasures more than lovers of God; Having a form of godliness, but denying the

5
00:00:30,432 --> 00:00:33,672
power thereof: from such turn away.

6
00:00:33,672 --> 00:00:40,775
For of this sort are they which creep into houses, and lead captive silly women laden with sins, led away with divers

7
00:00:40,775 --> 00:00:45,623
lusts, Ever learning, and never able to come to the knowledge of the truth.

8
00:00:45,623 --> 00:00:53,255
Now as Jannes and Jambres withstood Moses, so do these also resist the truth: men of corrupt minds, reprobate concerning

9
00:00:53,255 --> 00:01:01,271
the faith. But they shall proceed no further: for their folly shall be manifest unto all men, as theirs also was.

10
00:01:01,271 --> 00:01:09,407
But thou hast fully known my doctrine, manner of life, purpose, faith, longsuffering, charity, patience, Persecutions,

11
00:01:09,407 --> 00:01:17,351
afflictions, which came unto me at Antioch, at Iconium, at Lystra; what persecutions I endured: but out of them all the

12
00:01:17,351 --> 00:01:24,648
Lord delivered me. Yea, and all that will live godly in Christ Jesus shall suffer persecution.

13
00:01:24,648 --> 00:01:30,216
But evil men and seducers shall wax worse and worse, deceiving, and being deceived.

14
00:01:30,216 --> 00:01:36,479
But continue thou in the things which thou hast learned and hast been assured of, knowing of whom thou hast learned

15
00:01:36,479 --> 00:01:43,320
them; And that from a child thou hast known the holy scriptures, which are able to make thee wise unto salvation through

16
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:46,127
faith which is in Christ Jesus.

17
00:01:46,127 --> 00:01:53,711
All scripture is given by inspiration of God, and is profitable for doctrine, for reproof, for correction, for

18
00:01:53,711 --> 00:02:00,359
instruction in righteousness: That the man of God may be perfect, throughly furnished unto all good works.

